The former President, Goodluck Jonathan saved the country from plunging into political crisis, Gen. Abdulsalam Abubakar has said. Abubakar spoke today in Abuja at the one-day peace conference organised by the Goodluck Jonathan Foundation, with the theme “Peaceful Elections and National Development”. The former Head of State pointed out that Jonathan kept to his words that his ambition is not worth the blood of any Nigerian. He noted that the country has had its share of election violence in the past.